"To Antiochus Epiphanes" [Translated by C.P. Cavafy] (p. 3); "In a City of Asia Minor" (p. 4); "When Julian Observed Much Lukewarmness" (p. 5); "Young Men of Sidon (AD 400)" (p. 6); "Did He Die?" (p. 7); "The Sea in the Morning"; "Monotony" (p. 8); "The End" (p. 9) [Translated by G. A. Valassopoulo].

Dask. B41

