Yeros, Dimitris. _Shades of Love: Photographs Inspired by the Poems of C.P. Cavafy_. Translated from the Greek by David Connolly. Foreword by Edward Albee. Introduction by John Wood. San Rafael, California: Insight Editions, 2010. 165 p.

Contains: Introduction (pp. 12-20);

the following poems (in alphabetical order):

"Addition" (p. 130); "All Over" (p. 146); "And I Sat and Reclined on Their Beds" (p. 108); "Aristobulus" (p. 136); "Artificial Flowers" (p. 70); "Before Time Changes Them" (p. 112); "Birth of a Poem" (p. 52);

"Caesarion" (p. 96); "Candles" (p. 54); "Chandelier" (p. 74); "Che Fece ... Il Grand Rifiuto" (p. 150); "Craftsman of Craters" (p. 30); "Days of 1896" (p. 90); "Days of 1901" (p. 66); "Days of 1903" (p. 76); "Days of 1908" (p. 78); "Days of 1909, '10 and '11" (p. 122); "December, 1903" (p. 134);

"Far Back" (p. 40); "Grey" (p. 118); "He Asked about the Quality" (p. 72); "He Came to Read –" (p. 98); "House with Garden" (p. 64); "I Brought to Art" (p. 26); "I Went" (p. 92); "In a Town of Osroene" (p. 129); "In an Old Book --" (p. 50); "In Despair" (p. 106); "In the Boring Village" (p. 56); "In the Same Place" (p. 104); "In the Street" (p. 102); "Ionic" (p. 104); "Ithaca" (p. 24); "I've Looked so Much --" (p. 116);

"January 1904" (p. 144); "Lovely Flowers and White as Well Befitted" (p. 68); "Monotony" (p. 142); "Morning Sea" (p. 22); "Nothing concerning Lacedaemonians" (p. 152); "On Hearing of Love" (p. 94);

"Passing Through" (p. 46); "Portrait of a Twenty-Three-Year-Old Painted by His Friend of Similar Age, an Amateur (p. 110); "Remember, Body ..." (p. 48); "Return" (p. 58); "Sculptor of Tyana" (p. 138); "September, 1903" (p. 32); "Since Nine O'Clock --" (p. 28); "Sophist Leaving Syria" (p. 114); "So They May Come --" (p. 39); "Supplication" (p. 118);

"That's What" (p. 36); "The Bandaged Shoulder" (p. 124); "The Café Entrance" (p. 80); "The Favor of Alexander Balas" (p. 132); "The Mirror in the Entrance" (p. 100); "The Next Table" (p. 82); "The Souls of Old Men" (p. 60); "Theatre of Sidon (A.D. 400)" (p. 44); "Their Beginning" (p. 88); "Thermopylae" (p. 154); "To Remain" (p. 84); "To Sensual Pleasure" (p. 62); "Voices" (p. 34); "Walls" (p. 148); "[With My Soul on My Lips]" (p. 126).

Afterword by Dimitris Yeros (pp. 157-159).

ISBN 9781608870134

